1. gcloud auth list
    gcloud auth list displays all Google Cloud accounts that are currently authenticated on your local machine and shows which account is active.
    In simple terms: It tells you who is logged in to the gcloud CLI. 
    🔹 Switch Active Account, If you have multiple accounts and want to switch:
        gcloud config set account admin@company.com

🔹 Related Commands (Very Useful)
    ✅ Login to a new account:  gcloud auth login
    ✅ Activate service account (for automation):  gcloud auth activate-service-account --key-file=service-account-key.json
    ✅ Remove an account: gcloud auth revoke user@example.com

  Authentication and project selection are separate in GCP. After checking accounts, also check project: gcloud config list project
  Set project if needed: gcloud config set project my-project-id

  🔹 Real‑World Scenario: You run a deployment command and get a permission error. First thing to check: gcloud auth list
        ✅ Maybe the wrong account is active
        ✅ Switch to the correct one and retry

    🔹 Common Mistakes ❌
❌ Assuming the last logged‑in account is active
❌ Forgetting to switch accounts before production work
❌ Confusing project permissions with authentication




